    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "re library structure. Yes, can move into one repo, and then archive out the other ones.\r\n\r\nYou can have multiple nuget packages published from one repo; I have this in my Essential.Diagnostics project, that has a half dozen+ nuget packages.\r\n\r\nYou should also be able to set up local build references (pre-publish) with nuget config and local folder based package sources. Then just have build script build them in the correct order. \r\n\r\nThere are benefits both ways, e.g. keeping separate allows them to evolve and version separately, but either way is fine; as I said, I have other projects with one repo.\r\n\r\n(Actually, one of the reasons I pulled them out into separate repos originally was because of Nethermind, to make it possible to share components, in case that was the way we collaborated).",
